Strategic Planner, Asia Pacific (APHQ/201404/01/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00007277
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Apr 1 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Develop and maintain reports on market growth, business trends, competitive information to support Emerson Corporate and Emerson Process planning processes.
Facilitate development of key messages for site reviews and planning conferences.
Be an active member of Thought Leadership teams across AP; enable collaboration of ideas developed in these teams.
Provide strategic insights to Industry and Marketing Councils through industry segmentation, growth trends, develop analysis based on external reports.
Support any focus programs prioritized by President and/or AP Board through research and analysis and collaborate with Global, Regional and Business level planners to deliver results.
Requirements:
Bachelor/Master of Science in Engineering, MBA will be an advantage.
Some years of experience in similar industry will be a plus but candidates without experience will be considered.
High learning agility, good interpersonal savvy and organizational agility.